## 🌍 The Problem

Pakistan has **33 million diabetics** — the 3rd highest in the world.
Over **50% remain undiagnosed**.
Community health workers running rural screening camps have no fast,
intelligent triage tool. They screen patients manually with no way to
prioritize who needs urgent referral.

**GlucoseGuard PK changes that.**

---

## 🩺 What It Does

GlucoseGuard PK is a Machine Learning web application that:

- ✅ Predicts diabetes risk instantly from basic health indicators
- ✅ Shows a risk score (%) with Low / Medium / High classification
- ✅ Explains the TOP 5 risk drivers using SHAP explainability
- ✅ Recommends a clear next action (lifestyle advice / retest / refer for HbA1c)
- ✅ Supports population-level screening summaries for NGO camps
- ✅ Built for community health workers — no medical expertise required

---

## 📊 Machine Learning Pipeline

| Stage | Details |
|-------|---------|
| Dataset | CDC BRFSS 2015 — 80,000+ health records |
| Models Evaluated | Logistic Regression, Random Forest, XGBoost |
| Selected Model | Logistic Regression (highest diabetic recall: 76%) |
| Explainability | SHAP (LinearExplainer) |
| Class Imbalance | Handled with SMOTE |
| Deployment | Streamlit Cloud |

### Why Logistic Regression?
For a health screening tool, **missing a diabetic patient is dangerous**.
Logistic Regression achieved **76% recall on diabetic cases** vs
XGBoost's 18% — making it the right choice for triage.

